                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I have 6 AAs in the bank now.  I have 23 AAs spent (complete list at end of post), and I need to decide what to get next.  I am interested, in the near term, in getting SCM 3, MC up to 3 and then Gather Mana, Eldritch Rune to 3, Total Domination 2 and 3, Jewelcraft Master 2 and 3, Quick Buff up to 3, Combat Agility leading to Lightning Reflexes 5, and Dire Charm.
<br />

<br />
 My first impulse is to obey the received wisdom and get SCM 3.  However, I have watched were my mana goes when I get LOM pretty carefully.  My usual activities include: charm soloing in PoJ, XP grind groups in BoT, LDoN runs, and raids.  I almost never have mana trouble on raids or in BoT, at least not when it matters.  When I am LoM in LDoN or when charm soloing, my major expenses are re-Arcane Rune and re-Command of Druzzil.  Both spells are alteration.  My spec is in alteration as well.
<br />

<br />
 One of my major questions is: how much improvement is SCM 3 over SCM 2 in terms of it's effect on your spec spells?  I can imagine that it's quite a significant boost for non-spec spell use, but I just don't lose that much mana even in heavy mez conditions, and if SCM 3 doesn't do that much for spec spell use, then I'd rather get MGB, MC leading to GM, or Eldritch.
<br />

<br />
I have 23 AA spent in:
<br />

<br />
Run Speed 3
<br />
Regen 3
<br />
SCMastery 2
<br />
Channeling Focus 2
<br />
JCM 1
<br />
TD 1</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Ianthe Dawnglory
<br />
Enchanter
<br />
Ayonae Ro</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
