                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Candiarie wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">any thought into mgb if your sole chanter on raid? (normally me)</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Depends on how many groups in the raid.  I have been there, done that.  If there are 4 or less groups, I skip MGB and buff the groups directly.  If the raid is forming slowly, I skip MGB and buffs the groups as they form up.  Mana regens pretty quickly.  People always show up late and you need to group buff anyway even if you used MGB.  If you have 8 groups, single group buffing VoQ is a bit much.
<br />

<br />
Look at how you buff now, and determine if one MGB would make a big difference in how you buff.  You are in the best position to tell whether that is a good use of 9 AA points for you now.
<br />

<br />
Aallynth
<br />
65th chanter, Drinal</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
